{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771862684,"nonce":"4HXOiOx7IGLKyFU47BpjAQRL9ng=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87tKfVU","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/251","origin":"github"},"title":"Establish Architecture Decision Records and capture existing implicit decisions","message":"## Problem\n\nDesign decisions in this workspace are buried in issue comments, PR descriptions, and commit history. They're hard to find and at risk of being accidentally reverted — this has already happened (e.g., doc consolidation in #181 nearly undid intentional per-framework instruction duplication).\n\n## Solution\n\nAdopt Architecture Decision Records (ADRs) using the MADR format. Store in `docs/decisions/`, numbered sequentially. Plain markdown files, no tooling.\n\n## Tasks\n\n1. Create `docs/decisions/` and ADR-0001 (adopt ADRs as a practice)\n2. Write 4 retroactive ADRs capturing decisions that already exist implicitly:\n   - Worktree isolation over branch switching\n   - Per-framework agent instruction files are intentional\n   - Workspace infrastructure is project-agnostic\n   - Enforcement hierarchy for agent compliance (instructions → hooks → CI → containers)\n\n## Scope\n\nEach ADR should be short — context, decision, consequences. These are capturing *existing* decisions, not making new ones. The content is already known; the work is writing it down in a durable, discoverable format.\n\nParent tracking issue: #249\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}